Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Strip @rosemary{1/4%ounce} from stems and finely chop leaves. Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch wedges. Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with half the rosemary, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bake until lightly browned, ~{25-30%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

While potatoes cook, halve and core one @Granny Smith apple{1}. Grate onto a #paper towel{}, then squeeze out any excess moisture (you can do this over the sink). Put grated apple, @ground pork{20%ounce}, and @rosemary{2%tsp} in a large #bowl{}. Season with @salt{1%tsp}(kosher salt) and pepper. Combine mixture with your hands, then shape into four 1-inch-thick patties.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add burgers to pan and cook until no longer pink in center, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

Meanwhile, split @potato buns{4} in half horizontally and place on another baking sheet. Toast in oven until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Halve, core, and thinly slice remaining @Granny Smith apple{1}. In another large bowl, toss @mixed greens{4%ounce} and apple slices with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and @balsamic vinegar{4%tsp}(we sent more). Season with salt and pepper.

Spread buns with @mayonnaise{2%jar}. Serve burgers on buns with some of the dressed spring mix on top. Serve remaining salad and potatoes on the side.